class Solution {
    public int[] evenOddBit(int n) {
        int even = 0, odd = 0;
        int index = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            if ((n & 1) == 1) {
                if (index % 2 == 0) even++;
                else odd++;
            }
            n >>= 1;
            index++;
        }
        return new int[] {even, odd};
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterates through the binary representation of n, counting even and odd indices with value 1. Uses bitwise operations for efficiency.
